# Making BotNexus AI Studio Responsive

This document outlines the strategy for moving the current BotNexus AI Studio dashboard from a desktop-only layout to a fully responsive, mobile-first design.

## User Review Required

## Strategy Overview
We will implement a permanent Bottom Navigation Bar for mobile, introduce Framer Motion horizontal swiping for selecting Teams and Agents, add Top Tabs for Configuration/Testing panels, and place chat filters inside a Top Right Hamburger Menu. We will also rebrand everything to CustomerAGI using the new specific color palette.

Here is the breakdown of the Tailwind utility changes needed across the application to handle breakpoints (`sm`, [md](file:///c:/Users/Daniel%20Roldan%20CT/Desktop/Innagent%20%20CustomerAGI%20Proyect/Innagent/README.md), `lg`, `xl`).

### App Navigation (Mobile-First)
*   **[MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Daniel%20Roldan%20CT/Desktop/Innagent%20%20CustomerAGI%20Proyect/Innagent/App.tsx) & [components/Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Daniel%20Roldan%20CT/Desktop/Innagent%20%20CustomerAGI%20Proyect/Innagent/components/Sidebar.tsx)**
    *   Hide the left Sidebar entirely on mobile screens (`hidden md:flex`).
    *   Implement a **Bottom Navigation Bar** for mobile devices fixed to the bottom edge containing icons for Dashboard, Agents, Knowledge Base, and Settings.

